課程概述 Course Description
       Global Health has grown rapidly in the past few decades. Experts in this field have been exploring existed health related problems in the world and several social factors (like poverty, education, governance, culture and environment) which might result in these problems and have been trying to come up with some ideas/strategies to solve these problems. This course is designed to provide students with a basic understanding of what problems regarding global health are faced by people currently and what strategies can be used to resolve these problems. Many critical issues will be discussed in this course, including global burden of diseases, public policy analysis process, global healthcare system and global health promotion and disease prevention.  

課程學習目標 Course Objectives


